problem:
Equilateral triangle $ABC$ has been creased and folded so that vertex $A$ now rests at $A'$ on $\overline{BC}$ as shown.  If $BA' = 1$ and $A'C = 2,$ then find the length of crease $\overline{PQ}.$

[asy]
unitsize(1 cm);

pair A, Ap, B, C, P, Q;

A = 3*dir(60);
B = (0,0);
C = (3,0);
Ap = (1,0);
P = 8/5*dir(60);
Q = C + 5/4*dir(120);

draw(B--C--Q--P--cycle);
draw(P--Ap--Q);
draw(P--A--Q,dashed);

label("$A$", A, N);
label("$A'$", Ap, S);
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$P$", P, NW);
label("$Q$", Q, NE);
[/asy]

